"{\"uid\": \"outsideonline.com-outdoor-adventure-olympics-speed-climbing-paris-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"(Photo: Lena Drapella/IFSC) Speed climbers were dealt a rough hand at the Tokyo Olympics when they were pitted against lead and bouldering specialists in a strange three-discipline combined format.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 198, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"(Photo\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 6}, {\"ngram\": \"Lena Drapella/IFSC\", \"from\": 8, \"to\": 26}, {\"ngram\": \"Speed climbers\", \"from\": 28, \"to\": 42}, {\"ngram\": \"a rough hand\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 66}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 88}, {\"ngram\": \"lead and bouldering specialists\", \"from\": 119, \"to\": 150}, {\"ngram\": \"a strange three-discipline combined format\", \"from\": 154, \"to\": 196}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fortunately, speed climbing will be contested as a discipline all by itself at the Paris Olympics-proving, finally, who the best speed climbers in the world are.\", \"from\": 199, \"to\": 360, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"speed climbing\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 226}, {\"ngram\": \"a discipline\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 260}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics-proving\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 304}, {\"ngram\": \"the best speed climbers\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 342}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 355}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speed begins with a qualification round on August 5, then quarterfinal and final rounds on August 7.\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 464, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Speed\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 369}, {\"ngram\": \"a qualification\", \"from\": 382, \"to\": 397}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 413}, {\"ngram\": \"then quarterfinal and final rounds\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 451}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 461}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In total, 14 climbers per gender will be vying for the speed medals.\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 534, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"total\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 474}, {\"ngram\": \"14 climbers\", \"from\": 476, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"gender\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 498}, {\"ngram\": \"the speed medals\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 533}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are the climbers to watch.\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 566, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the climbers\", \"from\": 544, \"to\": 556}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Team USA's Sam Watson was just 15 years old, he was given the nickname \\\"Sub-Six Sam\\\" for breaking speed climbing's hallowed six-second mark.\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 573, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999681222113, \"rank\": 1.1398517072113956e-08, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 584, \"end\": 594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\", \"score\": 0.8551999212396617, \"rank\": 0.16931216931219462, \"text\": \"Sam Watson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the nickname\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 643}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Sub-Six Sam\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 656}, {\"ngram\": \"speed climbing's hallowed six-second mark\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 712}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the years that followed, he continued to set the new standard for American youth speed climbing-including setting a World Record in the Male Youth A category (5.37 seconds) at the Youth World Championships in Dallas, Texas, in 2022.\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 949, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 783, \"end\": 791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\", \"score\": 0.9621749816318166, \"rank\": 0.039311995127931536, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6631808\", \"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\"}, {\"begin\": 926, \"end\": 932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dallas\", \"score\": 0.9147320054622344, \"rank\": 0.09275495111167335, \"text\": \"Dallas\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dallas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dallas\"}, {\"begin\": 934, \"end\": 939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Longhorns\", \"score\": 0.9696706928977247, \"rank\": 0.03100993903740185, \"text\": \"Texas\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Longhorns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Texas_Longhorns\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the years\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 726}, {\"ngram\": \"the new standard\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"a World Record\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 845}, {\"ngram\": \"the Male Youth A category\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"5.37 seconds\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 888}, {\"ngram\": \"the Youth World Championships\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The youth accolades ensured Watson's place in speed climbing history, but he was only getting started.\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 1052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 978, \"end\": 984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Watson_(computer)\", \"score\": 0.9999833664652261, \"rank\": 1.662749082642483e-05, \"text\": \"Watson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Watson_(computer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Watson_(computer)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The youth accolades\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 969}, {\"ngram\": \"speed climbing history\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1018}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He eventually smashed John Brosler's long-standing (adult) American Record of 5.20 seconds with a run of 5.02.\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1163, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1112, \"end\": 1120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\", \"score\": 0.9621749816318166, \"rank\": 0.039311995127931536, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6631808\", \"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"John Brosler's long-standing (adult\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"5.20 seconds\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1143}, {\"ngram\": \"a run\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1154}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And then Watson went \\\"sub-5-seconds\\\"-a landmark achievement that only a handful of speed climbers have accomplished-and notched a new world record of 4.79 seconds at this year's speed World Cup in Wujiang, China.\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1173, \"end\": 1179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Watson_(computer)\", \"score\": 0.9999833664652261, \"rank\": 1.662749082642483e-05, \"text\": \"Watson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Watson_(computer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Watson_(computer)\"}, {\"begin\": 1361, \"end\": 1368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wujiang_District,_Suzhou\", \"score\": 0.9033921183319266, \"rank\": 0.0945638020833619, \"text\": \"Wujiang\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wujiang_District,_Suzhou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wujiang_District,_Suzhou\"}, {\"begin\": 1370, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9756901107685572, \"rank\": 0.024914584025486398, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"landmark achievement\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1223}, {\"ngram\": \"only a handful\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1243}, {\"ngram\": \"speed climbers\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1261}, {\"ngram\": \"a new world record\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"4.79 seconds\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1326}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's speed World Cup\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1357}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Watson should be considered the favorite in the men's field.\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1377, \"end\": 1383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Watson_(computer)\", \"score\": 0.9999833664652261, \"rank\": 1.662749082642483e-05, \"text\": \"Watson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Watson_(computer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Watson_(computer)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the men's field\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1436}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Career highlight (thus far):Time-wise, Sam Watson's high-water mark was setting that world record of 4.79.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1478, \"end\": 1488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\", \"score\": 0.8551999212396617, \"rank\": 0.16931216931219462, \"text\": \"Sam Watson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that world record\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1536}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(It's worth noting he's run even faster-4.66 seconds-in practice.)\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1612, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"even faster-4.66 seconds-in practice\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1610}]}, {\"sente