pedia.org/resource/Aspar\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Career highlight\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 2939}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3109}, {\"ngram\": \"the fastest men\", \"from\": 3125, \"to\": 3140}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3144, \"to\": 3153}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why he could win in Paris:Mawem is yet to go sub-5 in a competition, but he has come close.\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3192, \"end\": 3197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.426910836833163e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mawem\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3203}, {\"ngram\": \"a competition\", \"from\": 3226, \"to\": 3239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If some of the faster climbers in Paris stumble or false-start, look to Mawem to prevail by staying calm amid the intense Olympic pressure.\", \"from\": 3264, \"to\": 3403, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3298, \"end\": 3303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.426910836833163e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the faster climbers\", \"from\": 3275, \"to\": 3294}, {\"ngram\": \"Mawem\", \"from\": 3336, \"to\": 3341}, {\"ngram\": \"the intense Olympic pressure\", \"from\": 3374, \"to\": 3402}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2021, the speed fan base became captivated by the Indonesian team, as Indonesian climbers began chipping away at the world record at an unprecedented rate.\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3458, \"end\": 3468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"score\": 0.9953991972206081, \"rank\": 0.004621557819142702, \"text\": \"Indonesian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\"}, {\"begin\": 3478, \"end\": 3488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"score\": 0.9953991972206081, \"rank\": 0.004621557819142702, \"text\": \"Indonesian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the speed fan base\", \"from\": 3414, \"to\": 3432}, {\"ngram\": \"the world record\", \"from\": 3521, \"to\": 3537}, {\"ngram\": \"an unprecedented rate\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3562}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was exciting, and as viewers got caught up in the ever-changing world records, it became easy to overlook the fact that the Chinese team-traditionally a speed powerhouse-was largely absent from the circuit due to lingering travel restrictions from the COVID-19 pandemic.\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3691, \"end\": 3698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.972808332874374, \"rank\": 0.018771072766297556, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3819, \"end\": 3836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.9999999928268153, \"rank\": 7.173611819122032e-09, \"text\": \"COVID-19 pandemic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 3588, \"to\": 3595}, {\"ngram\": \"the ever-changing world records\", \"from\": 3613, \"to\": 3644}, {\"ngram\": \"the fact\", \"from\": 3673, \"to\": 3681}, {\"ngram\": \"traditionally a speed powerhouse\", \"from\": 3704, \"to\": 3736}, {\"ngram\": \"the circuit\", \"from\": 3761, \"to\": 3772}, {\"ngram\": \"lingering travel restrictions\", \"from\": 3780, \"to\": 3809}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once the China squad finally returned to the circuit in a big way, in 2022, it was Jinbao Long that led the charge.\", \"from\": 3838, \"to\": 3953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3847, \"end\": 3852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9756901107685572, \"rank\": 0.024914584025486398, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the circuit\", \"from\": 3879, \"to\": 3890}, {\"ngram\": \"a big way\", \"from\": 3894, \"to\": 3903}, {\"ngram\": \"the charge\", \"from\": 3942, \"to\": 3952}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Long made the podium at a trio of successive speed World Cups in 2022-in Villars, Chamonix, and Edinburgh-and suddenly, with Team China's reemergence, the dominance of the Indonesian team was not such a sure-thing anymore.\", \"from\": 3954, \"to\": 4176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4036, \"end\": 4044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chamonix\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3626546044585796e-41, \"text\": \"Chamonix\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chamonix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chamonix\"}, {\"begin\": 4079, \"end\": 4089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999985227752402, \"rank\": 1.4645115485138266e-06, \"text\": \"Team China\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_at_the_2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4126, \"end\": 4136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"score\": 0.9953991972206081, \"rank\": 0.004621557819142702, \"text\": \"Indonesian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 3964, \"to\": 3974}, {\"ngram\": \"a trio\", \"from\": 3978, \"to\": 3984}, {\"ngram\": \"successive speed World Cups\", \"from\": 3988, \"to\": 4015}, {\"ngram\": \"Villars\", \"from\": 4027, \"to\": 4034}, {\"ngram\": \"Edinburgh\", \"from\": 4050, \"to\": 4059}, {\"ngram\": \"the dominance\", \"from\": 4105, \"to\": 4118}, {\"ngram\": \"such a sure-thing\", \"from\": 4150, \"to\": 4167}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Long eventually earned a silver medal at the World Championships in 2023 and qualified for the Paris Olympics, and it feels like he's just starting to hit his stride.\", \"from\": 4177, \"to\": 4343, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a silver medal\", \"from\": 4200, \"to\": 4214}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Championships\", \"from\": 4218, \"to\": 4241}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 4268, \"to\": 4286}, {\"ngram\": \"his stride\", \"from\": 4332, \"to\": 4342}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fans can expect him to push the pace in Paris-and, along with his teammate Peng Wu, perhaps deliver multiple sub-5 runs-while being one of the most formidable challengers in the field.\", \"from\": 4344, \"to\": 4528, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4424, \"end\": 4426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Wu\", \"score\": 0.9974214431791552, \"rank\": 0.002584985218590189, \"text\": \"Wu\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Wu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Wu\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fans\", \"from\": 4344, \"to\": 4348}, {\"ngram\": \"the pace\", \"from\": 4372, \"to\": 4380}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris\", \"from\": 4384, \"to\": 4389}, {\"ngram\": \"his teammate\", \"from\": 4406, \"to\": 4418}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple sub-5 runs\", \"from\": 4444, \"to\": 4463}, {\"ngram\": \"the most formidable challengers\", \"from\": 4483, \"to\": 4514}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 4518, \"to\": 4527}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Career highlight (thus far):Jinbao Long won a World Cup gold medal in Chamonix in 2022.\", \"from\": 4530, \"to\": 4617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4600, \"end\": 4608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chamonix\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3626546044585796e-41, \"text\": \"Chamonix\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chamonix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chamonix\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Career highlight\", \"from\": 4530, \"to\": 4546}, {\"ngram\": \"a World Cup gold medal\", \"from\": 4574, \"to\": 4596}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why he could win in Paris:Long has repeatedly notched times near the five-second mark, and he is undoubtedly capable of running even faster.\", \"from\": 4619, \"to\": 4759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4639, \"end\": 4644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.426910836833163e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Long\", \"from\": 4645, \"to\": 4649}, {\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 4673, \"to\": 4678}, {\"ngram\": \"the five-second mark\", \"from\": 4684, \"to\": 4704}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That mix of speed and uniformity could be his key to getting the gold medal.\", \"from\": 4760, \"to\": 4836, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That mix\", \"from\": 4760, \"to\": 4768}, {\"ngram\": \"speed\", \"from\": 4772, \"to\": 4777}, {\"ngram\": \"uniformity\", \"from\": 4782, \"to\": 4792}, {\"ngram\": \"his key\", \"from\": 4802, \"to\": 4809}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold medal\", \"from\": 4821, \"to\": 4835}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It does not hurt that his compatriot and fellow Olympian Peng Wu recently clocked a blazing time of 4.83 seconds at the Olympic Qualifier Series.\", \"from\": 4837, \"to\": 4982, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4885, \"end\": 4893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999655665311, \"rank\": 3.4433423142721426e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 4899, \"end\": 4901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Wu\", \"score\": 0.9974214431791552, \"rank\": 0.002584985218590189, \"text\": \"Wu\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Wu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eastern_Wu\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his compatriot\", \"from\": 4859, \"to\": 4873}, {\"ngram\": \"a blazing time\", \"from\": 4919, \"to\": 4933}, {\"ngram\": \"4.83 seconds\", \"from\": 4937, \"to\": 4949}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Qualifier Series\", \"from\": 4953, \"to\": 4981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps that will give Long some healthy added pressure and motivation in Paris.\", \"from\": 4983, \"to\": 5063, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5057, \"end\": 5062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.426910836833163e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Long\", \"from\": 5006, \"to\": 5010}, {\"ngram\": \"some healthy added pressure\", \"from\": 5011, \"to\": 5038}, {\"ngram\": \"motivation\", \"from\": 5043, \"to\": 5053}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a fascinating blip in the history of speed climbing's fastest times.\", \"from\": 5065, \"to\": 5142, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a fascinating blip\", \"from\": 5074, \"to\": 5092}, {\"ngram\": \"the history\", \"from\": 5096, \"to\": 5107}, {\"ngram\": \"speed climbing's fastest times\", \"from\": 5111, \"to\": 5141}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From approximately 2015 to 2021, the best times at World Cups typically hovered in the mid-5-second realm (5.76, 5.62, 5.55, 5.48, etc.).\", \"from\": 5143, \"to\": 5280, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the best times\", \"from\": 5176, \"to\": 5190}, {\"ngram\": \"World Cups\", \"from\": 5194, \"to\": 5204}, {\"ngram\": \"the mid-5-second realm\", \"from\": 5226, \"to\": 5248}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But then, at a World Cup in Salt Lake City in 2021, Indonesia's Veddriq Leonardo set a new world record-5.20 seconds-and ushered in a whole new era of speed climbing.\", \"from\": 5281, \"to\": 5447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5309, \"end\": 5323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"score\": 0.9280813002532233, \"rank\": 0.07749180995995396, \"text\": \"Salt Lake City\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salt_Lake_City\"}, {\"begin\": 5333, \"end\": 5342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia_national_badminton_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999309111468, \"rank\": 6.907786125488605e-08, \"text\": \"Indonesia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia_national_badminton_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia_national_badminton_team\"}, {\"begin\": 5345, \"end\": 5361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veddriq_Leonardo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Veddriq Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veddriq_Leonardo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veddriq_Leonardo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a World Cup\", \"from\": 5294, \"to\": 5305}, {\"ngram\": \"a new world\", \"from\": 5366, \"to\": 5377}, {\"ngram\": \"a whole new era\", \"from\": 5413, \"to\": 5428}, {\"ngram\": \"speed climbing\", \"from\": 5432, \"to\": 5446}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Suddenly there was no performative ceiling, and fans and pundits had to recalibrate perceptions of human potential in the speed discipline.\", \"from\": 5448, \"to\": 5587, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no performative ceiling\", \"from\": 5467, \"to\": 5490}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 5496, \"to\": 5500}, {\"ngram\": \"pundits\", \"from\": 5505, \"to\": 5512}, {\"ngram\": \"perceptions\", \"from\": 5532, \"to\": 5543}, {\"ngram\": \"human potential\", \"from\": 5547, \"to\": 5562}, {\"ngram\": \"the speed discipline\", \"from\": 5566, \"to\": 5586}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just as the sports world clamored to see a sprinter run a mile in less than four minutes in the spring of 1954, comp fans longed to witness a speed climber ascend a 15-meter wall in less than five seconds.\", \"from\": 5588, \"to\": 5793, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sports world\", \"from\": 5596, \"to\": 5612}, {\"ngram\": \"a sprinter\", \"from\": 5629, \"to\": 5639}, {\"ngram\": \"a mile\", \"from\": 5644, \"to\": 5650}, {\"ngram\": \"less than four minutes\", \"from\": 5654, \"to\": 5676}, {\"ngram\": \"the spring\", \"from\": 5680, \"to\": 5690}, {\"ngram\": \"comp fans\", \"from\": 5700, \"to\": 5709}, {\"ngram\": \"a speed climber\", \"from\": 5728, \"to\": 5743}, {\"ngram\": \"a 15-meter wall\", \"from\": 5751, \"to\": 5766}, {\"ngram\": \"less than five seconds\", \"from\": 5770, \"to\": 5792}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fittingly, when it finally happened, it was Leonardo who successfully accomplished it, clocking a run-time of 4.98 seconds at a World Cup in Seoul in 2023.\", \"from\": 5794, \"to\": 5949, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5838, \"end\": 5846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.42327114666832e-12, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 5935, \"end\": 5940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seoul\", \"score\": 0.9979753645250037, \"rank\": 0.0018432970436012502, \"text\": \"Seoul\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seoul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seoul\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a run-time\", \"from\": 5890, \"to\": 5900}, {\"ngram\": \"4.98 seconds\", \"from\": 5904, \"to\": 5916}, {\"ngram\": \"a World Cup\", \"from\": 5920, \"to\": 5931}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even though Leonardo no longer holds the world record (having relinquished it to Sam Watson earlier this year), Leonardo should still be considered one of the fastest men in the Olympic field and one of the favorites to win gold.\", \"from\": 5950, \"to\": 6179, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5962, \"end\": 5970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.42327114666832e-12, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 6031, \"end\": 6041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\", \"score\": 0.8551999212396617, \"rank\": 0.16931216931219462, \"text\": \"Sam Watson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\"}, {\"begin\": 6062, \"end\": 6070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.42327114666832e-12, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world record\", \"from\": 5987, \"to\": 6003}, {\"ngram\": \"the fastest men\", \"from\": 6105, \"to\": 6120}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic field\", \"from\": 6124, \"to\": 6141}, {\"ngram\": \"the favorites\", \"from\": 6153, \"to\": 6166}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 6174, \"to\": 6178}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Career highlight (thus far):Veddriq Leonardo broke his own world record last year, which lowered his personal best time from 4.90 seconds to 4.85 seconds.\", \"from\": 6181, \"to\": 6335, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6209, \"end\": 6225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veddriq_Leonardo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Veddriq Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veddriq_Leonardo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veddriq_Leonardo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his own world record\", \"from\": 6232, \"to\": 6252}, {\"ngram\": \"his personal best time\", \"from\": 6278, \"to\": 6300}, {\"ngram\": \"4.90 seconds\", \"from\": 6306, \"to\": 6318}, {\"ngram\": \"4.85 seconds\", \"from\": 6322, \"to\": 6334}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why he could win in Paris:Aside from Sam Watson, there is nobody better than Veddriq Leonardo in the men's field at consistently notching runs of sub-5.\", \"from\": 6337, \"to\": 6489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6357, \"end\": 6362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.426910836833163e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6374, \"end\": 6384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\", \"score\": 0.8551999212396617, \"rank\": 0.16931216931219462, \"text\": \"Sam Watson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Watson_(political_activist)\"}, {\"begin\": 6414, \"end\": 6430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veddriq_Leonardo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Veddriq Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veddriq_Leonardo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veddriq_Leonardo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nobody\", \"from\": 6395, \"to\": 6401}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's field\", \"from\": 6434, \"to\": 6449}, {\"ngram\": \"consistently notching runs\", \"from\": 6453, \"to\": 6479}, {\"ngram\": \"sub-5\", \"from\": 6483, \"to\": 6488}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Poland's Aleksandra Miroslaw once had an undefeated streak in speed World Cups that stretched from 2019 to the tail-end of the 2023 season.\", \"from\": 6491, \"to\": 6630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6491, \"end\": 6497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9992100685574922, \"rank\": 0.000790555921404749, \"text\": \"Poland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 6500, \"end\": 6519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandra_Miros\\u0142aw\", \"score\": 0.9999999356959982, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aleksandra Miroslaw\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandra_Miros\\u0142aw\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksandra_Miros\\u0142aw\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an undefeated streak\", \"from\": 6529, \"to\": 6549}, {\"ngram\": \"speed World Cups\", \"from\": 6553, \"to\": 6569}, {\"ngram\": \"the tail-end\", \"from\": 6598, \"to\": 6610}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2023 season\", \"from\": 6614, \"to\": 6629}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a discipline rife with stumbles, slips, and false-starts, that is a remarkable statistic.\", \"from\": 6631, \"to\": 6723, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a discipline rife\", \"from\": 6634, \"to\": 6651}, {\"ngram\": \"stumbles\", \"from\": 6657, \"to\": 6665}, {\"ngram\": \"slips\", \"from\": 6667, \"to\": 6672}, {\"ngram\": \"false-starts\", \"from\": 6678, \"to\": 6690}, {\"ngram\": \"a remarkable statistic\", \"from\": 6700, \"to\": 6722}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Add to it that Miroslaw also owned the world record for part of that time-and still owns it.\", \"from\": 6724, \"to\": 6816, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Miroslaw\", \"from\": 6739, \"to\": 6747}, {\"ngram\": \"the world record\", \"from\": 6759, \"to\": 6775}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 6780, \"to\": 6784}, {\"ngram\": \"that time\", \"from\": 6788, \"to\": 6797}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She also won World Championships in 2018 and 2019.\", \"from\": 6817, \"to\": 6867, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"World Championships\", \"from\": 6830, \"to\": 6849}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such accolades combine to form a resume that might never be duplicated on the comp scene.\", \"from\": 6868, \"to\": 6957, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Such accolades\", \"from\": 6868, \"to\": 6882}, {\"ngram\": \"a resume\", \"from\": 6899, \"to\": 6907}, {\"ngram\": \"the comp scene\", \"from\": 6942, \"to\": 6956}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They also make Miroslaw an intimidating presence for anyone that will line up next to her for a race at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 6958, \"to\": 7081, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Miroslaw\", \"from\": 6973, \"to\": 6981}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 7011, \"to\": 7017}, {\"ngram\": \"a race\", \"from\": 7052, \"to\": 7058}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 7062, \"to\": 7080}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Additionally, Miroslaw will enter the Paris Olympics as a highly experienced competitor, as she participated in the Tokyo Olympics in 2021 (and set the current Olympic record of 6.84 seconds).\", \"from\": 7082, \"to\": 7274, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Miroslaw\", \"from\": 7096, \"to\": 7104}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 7116, \"to\": 7134}, {\"ngram\": \"a highly experienced competitor\", \"from\": 7138, \"to\": 7169}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 7194, \"to\